    Get multiple datasets

    Usage

    get_many_data(
  dataset,
  from = NULL,
  to = NULL,
  col_list = NULL,
  save_where = c("renviron", "disk", "both", "no_message"),
  memory_warning_limit = 900
)

    Arguments

    dataset

    string

    from

    string specific version of any survey

    to

    string specific version of any survey

    col_list

    character vector by default is all columns. The possible values can be obtained through the get_columns function

    save_where

    string by default is "renviron", the possible values are "renviron","disk","both", "no_message".

    memory_warning_limit

    numeric by default is 900 mb, changes the data limit in warning megabytes to prevent excessive loading of the R environment memory

    versions

    character vector with specific versions of any survey

    Value

    list containing all the datasets between the from and to parameters
